<br/><a href="/db/classes.html?class=7;mid=1108509103184459006;page=1;howmany=50#1108509103184459006"><img alt="" title="Use this to create a link to this post" src="/shared/garrowrt.png" border="0" height="9" width="11" /> Link to this post</a>

<br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td>
<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>I'm a Lvl 16 DE Cleric and would like some advise on timing my Healing spells.  I haven't grouped yet and want to be on top of my game when I finally start grouping.  At what % should my Tank be before I start healing?  Also what spells should I have memorized?  I have been hunting in Kurn's Tower but am going to try Paludal Caverns.  <br /> <br />P.S. What is a good Quest to do? Any Tradeskill advise would be great. <br /> <br />Dark Elf Cleric &quot;Seyll&quot; <br />Level 16</p>
</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td class="fs8"></td><td align="right" class="fs8" >4 replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2"><a name="1108527566228716744"></a>
		   <span class="sm">Posted: Feb 16th  2005 at 12:19am EDT<span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=7;mid=1108509103184459006;num=4;page=1;post=1;replyto=1108527566228716744"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a>    </span></span></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform2" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By: </span><a href="/db/poster.html?user=512569"><span class="">Sheritanas</span></a><b><span class=""></span></b><br />4 posts
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent  </span><br />
<br/><a href="/db/classes.html?class=7;mid=1108509103184459006;page=1;howmany=50#1108527566228716744"><img alt="" title="Use this to create a link to this post" src="/shared/garrowrt.png" border="0" height="9" width="11" /> Link to this post</a>

<br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td>
<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>I know I'm not the best to help with this since there are others here that have played Clerics for a lot longer than I have. When you get higher, especially after lvl 39 when you get Complete Heal, then you can really start having fun with your healing. Complete Heal takes 10 seconds to cast, as long as you're not interrupted, and so you can wait (always ask your tank's opinion on this) until their 30s for a heal. Or lower.. the guy I usually group with takes his heals in the 20s. <br /> <br />But at your level, I'd be cautious. Your healing spell might not do as much if you have a tank with temperance on and you can find yourself casting it over and over to get his/her HP up to a safe level. Always watch your mana bar because of it.. nothing sucks mana like repeat heals.  <br /> <br />At level 16, the spells that I would have loaded would be: Healing, Smite, Soothe, Root and whatever else you think would be necessary. (Anyone else have input on this?) The camps in Paludal Caverns do not have undead, just bandits.. so you don't need your Undead spells there. Base your spell selection on two things 1) what classes are in your group, and 2) what type of mobs will you be facing. <br /> <br />Most likely you will spend most of your time medding in these younger levels. Personally, I think you should keep your 1h blunt skill up as much as you can as well. So if you get full mana, swing once or twice against a mob. Just don't pull aggro.. tanks don't like that. I was questioned in an Ldon once because I was up front with the tank, hitting for all I had on a mob. The entire group backed me up in the argument that clerics are not just wimpy healers.. we have other skills. Our nukes are not that bad, we know how to use our weapons.. we even have Undead Damage over Time spells. Plus we buff!  Definitely a multi-talented class. Only thing I haven't learned is how to solo well, I'll get that one day. <br /> <br />So don't be afraid to do some melee as long as your mana allows it, it certainly helps if you find yourself in a position where you need to defend yourself later on. If your weapon procs, make sure its a small proc.. don't take aggro from your tanks by using a powerful weapon.   <br /> <br />As for Tradeskills.. I don't know much on them. I do Fletching with my warrior but that's it. I'd probably do Tailoring on my cleric to start him out if I ever decide to actually start a skill. Perhaps someone else has some advice on that. Enjoy your cleric, it is a fun class to have.</p>
<br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Sheritanas Amanyar, 58 High Elf Cleric of Tunare <br />Sheritan Eldacar, 57 Wood Elf Warrior of Tunare <br />Delnozz Dracuul, 46 Dark Elf Necromancer of Innoruuk</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td class="fs8">Posting from Bertoxxulous</td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
